      \begin {tikzpicture}[diagram]
        \node  (u) {$u$};
        \node  (Pu) [below = 1cm of u] {$Pu$};
        \node  (x) [right = 1.5cm of Pu] {$x$};
        \draw [lies over] (u) to (Pu);
        \draw [->] (Pu) to node [below] {$\phi _{u}$} (x);
      \end {tikzpicture}

A morphism (u,\phi _{u})\xrightarrow [f]{} (v,\phi _{v}) over f : x \to  y is given by a morphism h : u\to  v that lies over f modulo the isomorphisms \phi _{u},\phi _{v} in sense depicted below:







